552
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,500
Excuse me, can you stop arguing now?

553
00:37:41,500 --> 00:37:43,100
My blood is draining, guys.

554
00:37:43,100 --> 00:37:44,100
Okay.

555
00:37:44,100 --> 00:37:46,800
Uncle, be careful. He is afraid of blood.

556
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:50,200
Hold on. I have to disinfect you with iodine.

557
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:53,100
It hurts.

558
00:37:53,100 --> 00:37:54,300
Are you a doctor?

559
00:37:54,300 --> 00:37:56,600
I'm not, but this is just a skin injury.

560
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,800
I can treat it for you.

561
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:08,800
Okay. Turn around.

562
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:12,600
- There is no blood? 
 - Yes, it's all bound up.

563
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,300
You're good at binding up.

564
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,700
You're more professional than doctors.

565
00:38:19,700 --> 00:38:21,200
Bro, what's the name of your team?

566
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:23,400
I've never seen your uniform.

567
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:26,000
We are the Light Chaser Rescue Team.

568
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,800
This is our team uniform.

569
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:28,900
Cool.

570
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:31,000
I envied those who can wear uniforms when I was little.

571
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,400
Can I join you?

572
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:34,000
Of course.

573
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,800
But you need to pass the tests.

574
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:39,200
Uncle, forget it. Look at him.

575
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:41,700
He is so weak, and is afraid of blood.

576
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:44,000
He needs someone else to save him.

577
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,800
If you talk like this, I'll sue you for insulting my personality.

578
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:48,600
Mr. Lawyer, there is such a regulation in the law. Right?

579
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:51,400
Article 246 of the Criminal Law, crime of insulting others.

580
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,600
Do you hear it?

581
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:54,600
Uncle, look. He is evil.

582
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,600
Even if he passes the tests, you can't let him join.

583
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:58,000
Your uncle isn't the one to decide it.

584
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:00,800
My uncle is the captain, what?

585
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:03,600
Doctor, how's my sister?

586
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:06,800
The operation is still in progress, but the patient needs more blood.

587
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,400
Our bloodstock is not enough.

588
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,300
Who is blood type A?

589
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:14,600
I'm type O, for emergency use.

590
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:16,800
I'm type AB.

591
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:19,400
Is there a type A? Type A is the best.

592
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,400
What blood type are you?

593
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:23,000
- I... 
 - Are you type A?

594
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,400
You can draw his blood.

595
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:26,500
But I'm still injured.

596
00:39:26,500 --> 00:39:28,800
You won't die because of it. It's urgent to save lives now.

597
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:32,300
- But I've drained so much blood, I... 
 -  Please.

598
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:33,800
Save my sister.

599
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,400
I'll be straightforward.

600
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,800
Your sister is innocent.

601
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,800
We want to save her life, it doesn't mean we can forgive you.

602
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:41,100
Enough, Dingding.

603
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:43,400
I'll ask the team members to donate blood.

604
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,800
Okay.

605
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:46,600
Follow me.

606
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,000
Hurry up.

607
00:39:48,800 --> 00:39:50,300
Be careful.

608
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,500
You are awake?

609
00:40:02,500 --> 00:40:05,200
Where am I?

610
00:40:05,200 --> 00:40:07,800
The field hospital. You passed out after donating blood.

611
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,900
But don't worry. You drank dextrose liquid.

612
00:40:09,900 --> 00:40:12,900
The doctor said you'll be fine when you woke up.

613
00:40:12,900 --> 00:40:16,200
Well, have some rest here.

614
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:19,700
I need to go back to Linjiang.

615
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:21,000
You can't leave.

616
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,200
Who will take care of me if you leave? Let's leave together.

617
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:25,000
Why are you sticking to me now?

618
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,200
I have something urgent to do.

619
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:28,600
You asked me to donate blood. You can't leave.

620
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:30,400
- Let me go. 
 - No.

621
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,800
Let me go...

622
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,200
No.

623
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:40,000
Okay, I won't go.

624
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:45,900

625
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:06,700
Dr. Zhan, how's my sister?

626
00:41:06,700 --> 00:41:08,900
She is out of danger now.

627
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:14,600
Thanks. Thank you.

628
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:19,500
If you really want to thank me, do something for the disaster area.

629
00:41:19,500 --> 00:41:21,100
When the principal was dying,

630
00:41:21,100 --> 00:41:23,500
he was still caring about Ms. Luo and kids in the disaster area.

631
00:41:23,500 --> 00:41:26,600
Okay. Okay.

632
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,600
Thank you.

633
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:58,600
Back then, the principal made efforts

634
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:03,600
to build this Hope Primary School.

635
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:08,700
But now, it's collapsed.

636
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:14,340
The kids need  to travel a long distance to go to school.

637
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:21,900
Chief, here.

638
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:28,800
This... This is my gift for the village.

639
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:33,200
I hope the principal may rest in peace.

640
00:42:33,200 --> 00:42:36,800
I believe the principal also hopes

641
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:39,800
the school can be rebuilt as soon as possible.

